# Card — Styles

CSS file: `@acko/css/card.css`

## CSS Classes

### Base
`.acko-card` — border-radius `--radius-4xl` (20px), overflow hidden.

### Variants

| Class | Fill | Stroke | Shadow |
|-------|------|--------|--------|
| `.acko-card-default` | `--color-card-bg` | `1px solid --color-card-border` | none |
| `.acko-card-outline` | `transparent` | `1px solid --color-card-outline-border` | none |
| `.acko-card-elevated` | `--color-card-elevated-bg` | none | `0px 2px 16px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04)` |
| `.acko-card-demoted` | `--color-card-demoted-bg` | `1px solid --color-card-demoted-border` | none |

Design intent: On a `--color-surface` page, default cards use `--color-card-bg` fill with a `--color-card-border` stroke — the border is *lighter* than the fill, creating a floating highlight edge.

