### Nested Radius Rule

**Formula:** `inner radius = outer radius (20px) − card padding`

| Card Padding | Inset Token | Computed Radius |
|---|---|---|
| `pad-sm` (12px) | `--radius-inset-sm` | 8px (`--radius-lg`) |
| `pad-md` (16px) | `--radius-inset-md` | 4px (`--radius-sm`) |
| `pad-lg` (24px) | `--radius-inset-lg` | 0px (flat) |

Any rectangular child element (icon box, image, inset panel) uses the matching `--radius-inset-*` token for its card padding level.

**Exempt**: Badges, avatars — keep their own intentional radius.

### CTA Button Placement Rule

A pill button (`--radius-full`) inside a card must **never touch the card edge**. Full-width buttons live inside the padded content zone — the card's padding provides the breathing room between the pill corner and the card corner.

- Minimum card padding when a CTA is present: `pad-md` (16px)
- `fullWidth` button = full width of the **content area**, not the card itself
- Buttons with `pad-none` cards: **not allowed** — use `overflow: hidden` on the card and drop the button's own radius as a last resort

## Theme Mapping

**Light:** fill grey-50 (`--color-card-bg`), border grey-white (`--color-card-border`).

**Dark:** fill grey-650 (`--color-card-bg`), border grey-600 (`--color-card-border`). Automatic via semantic token remapping in `tokens.css`.
